Package: MESgenCov
Type: Package
Title: Generates input for the MES problem
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Hessa Al-Thani [aut, cre]
	      Jon Lee        [aut]
Maintainer: Hessa Al-Thani <hessa.k.h9@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: MVN, stringr, lubridate, EnvStats, rmatio, LambertW
Suggests: R.rsp
VignetteBuilder: R.rsp
ByteCompile: true
Description: This package performs multivariate normality tests on cavariance matricies produced by pollutant monitoring data.
            Using the MVN and EnvStats package a user can asses the normality of the multivariate data and make changes to gaussianize the final multivariate distribution.
            The aim of this package is to streamline the process of getting a validinput for the Maximum Entropy Sampling Problem (MESP).
